# Cursor Rules for GitGym

## Project Context
GitGym is a Git learning sandbox with React 19 + TypeScript frontend and Go backend.

## Code Style
- TypeScript: Strict mode, no @ts-ignore, functional components
- Go: Standard layout, docstrings for exports
- CSS: Use CSS variables (--bg-primary, --text-primary, etc.)

## Patterns
- Backend: Command Pattern (implement git.Command interface)
- Frontend: Context for state, services for API calls
- Testing: Playwright E2E, Go integration tests

## File Naming
- Components: PascalCase.tsx
- Utilities: camelCase.ts
- Go: lowercase.go

## Important Files
- Frontend state: src/context/GitAPIContext.tsx
- Backend dispatcher: internal/git/engine.go
- Types: src/types/gitTypes.ts, internal/git/types.go

## Commands
- Dev: `npm run dev` (frontend), `go run cmd/server/main.go` (backend)
- Test: `npm run test:e2e`, `go test ./...`
- Build: `npm run build`, `docker compose up --build`

## Common Tasks
- Add Git command: Create file in backend/internal/git/commands/, implement Command interface
- Add component: Create in src/components/, use useGit() hook for state
- Add API endpoint: Modify backend/internal/server/handlers.go
